title: Cubs beat Brewers, try to keep up in race to host wild card (Yahoo Sports)
text: Posts: 54,015 Cubs beat Brewers, try to keep up in race to host wild card (Yahoo Sports) Jake Arrieta struck out seven in six strong innings, and the Chicago Cubs beat the Milwaukee Brewers 6-1 on Friday night as they tried to keep up with Pittsburgh in the race to host the NL wild card game. Anthony Rizzo had two hits and three RBIs, including a solo homer into the Cubs bullpen in right in the fourth off Ariel Pena (2-1). Arrieta (22-6) allowed two singles in his final tuneup before the postseason.
